How to use:
1. Enter your base costs Add your unit cost (from your supplier) and your shipping costs (first + additional items). You can get both directly from your supplier.
2. Set your pricing Enter how much you’ll charge per unit and for customer shipping. This is where you control your margins. 
You’ll instantly see your profit!
Optional:
3. Add fees  Include platform fees, fulfilment, inventory costs, and tax if needed. Quick links: Etsy, Amazon (FBM/FBA), eBay, Shopify
4. Add discounts Test customer offers or enter supplier discounts (including batch) to see how they impact margins at different quantities.
5. Add ads info Enter your target CPA and select an expected order quantity (at target AOV) to see your max CPA and break-even ROAS.
